Last night U.S. cities along the Gulf of Mexico from Alabama to eastern Texas were on  storm watch for Hurricane Andrew which early yesterday caused at least eight deaths  and heavy property damage in southern Florida.
Florida Power estimates that 1.2  million of its customers are without power.
There was concern last night that the  hurricane might hit New Orleans which is especially vulnerable because of its low-lying  location.
It could also threaten offshore oil production facilities along the Gulf coast of  Louisiana and Texas.
A British insurance adjuster estimates that total losses,  concentrated among U. S. Insurers, could exceed $15 billion. 
